	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" > <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Bjorne </i><br />
<b>It's long been determined that taunt does nothing if you already hold aggro on the mob.</b><hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
Well, there are still people who insist that this isn't true and really believe that a successful taunt is +100 aggro or some such.  The purpose of the test was really to put that argument to bed finally.  <br />
<br />
Although some of these results on these tests weren't what was expected, there hasn't been anything that indicates that it's a good idea to mindlessly mash the taunt button while you already have aggro, so I think that we were right about that at least.<br />
<br />
EDIT:  I would buy Frodlin's theory about mashing on raids where there's a lot of clerics, wizards, etc gaining aggro from a distance.  I can't say whether it's true or not, but it makes sense.</font></p>
	
